Petasma with lateral lobule roughly trapezoidal, conspicuously surpassing median lobe; ventral costa as long as lateral lobule, attached along almost entire length, with tip turning slightly mesially. First and second abdominal somites dorsally rounded, third to sixth somites dorsally carinate, carina of third somite extending only along posterior two-thirds, almost indistinct, four posterior somites ending in sharp spine. Telson bearing 4 pairs of movable lateral spines in posterior half (modified from
Pérez Farfante & Kensley, 1997
).
